answers.text: Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces in Europe

qas.question: What was the name of the North African invasion Eisenhower oversaw?

context: Dwight <a1_0>David<a1_0/> "<a0_0>Ike<a0_0/>" Eisenhower (/ˈaɪzənˌhaʊ.ər/ EYE-zən-HOW-ər; October 14, 1890 – March 28, 1969) was an American politician and general who served as the 34th President of the United States from <a2_0>1953<a2_0/> until 1961. He was a five-star general in the United States Army during World War II and served as <a3_0>Supreme Commander of the Allied Forces in Europe<a3_0/>. He was responsible for planning and supervising the invasion of North Africa in <a4_0>Operation Torch<a4_0/> in 1942–43 and the successful invasion of France and Germany in 1944–45 from the Western Front. In 1951, he became the first Supreme Commander of NATO.
